letting it go over your head hi im a female bus driver and l work on one bad route i got threatened lastnight and also someone handed in a knife which is all too common on this route it can be very intimidating but you have to act like you dont give a shite and act tough but l find this very hard anyone any suggestions on how to let things just go over your head serious replies only please i consider myself to be polite and kind to my passengers i try and make them as comfortable as poss try not to miss stops but sometimes it happens but even so we dont deserve the abuse that we get i answered a posting where people were being very unkind to bus drivers yesterday complaining about them not stopping etc my ex husband was a bus driver though so i know how it really is he got abused both mentally and physically and missed a ball bearing shot from a gun at his head by inches i wouldn't do your job hunny and i have absolutely no idea how you let this kind of stuff go over your head i am so sorry i cant help but i am with you in spirit i have the feeling you either have the confidence of appearing hard or you don't its not something you can necessarily learn i hope i am wrong Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Sin City Theory of conduct Shaggy dog story Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Kasparov versus The World Hey Jude Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Social rule Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Religion Humphrey Bogart YuYu Hakusho The nature of God in Western theology Dualism (philosophy of mind) Evil Transactional analysis The Subtle Knife Bus stop Marilyn Monroe Friends Domestic violence Cindy Sheehan Abortion debate Rosa Parks 2000 Australian Grand Prix The Inside 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Theodicy Milton H. Erickson Poker jargon Plame affair Abu Ghraib torture and prisoner abuse Piccolo Junior Saga Soul Knife The Amber Spyglass Boston Public Ex-gay Goodness and value theory Alcoholics Anonymous Bus Moral Politics Characters of